### High-Priority Items Requiring Attention

1. **[1.1 / 3.2] Blocking sync call in async endpoint** — `graph.invoke()` is synchronous but called from `async def instruct`. Either make the endpoint `def` (not async) so FastAPI runs it in a threadpool, or use `asyncio.to_thread(graph.invoke, ...)`.

2. **[2.1] No error handling around `graph.invoke()`** — Any graph/LLM failure results in unstructured 500 errors. Needs try/except with a structured error response.

3. **[2.3] Missing required state fields in `graph.invoke()` input** — The `AgentState` defines `task_id`, `retry_count`, `current_phase`, `agent_role`, and `files_modified` as required, but the invoke call only provides `messages`. Needs investigation to confirm LangGraph handles this gracefully.
